docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: We are, so it seems, what we are told to eat. We have become a nation of people fixed on, if not obsessed with, the nutritional value of the foods we eat. We are hit left and right with information about which foods are healthy and which are not, which help prevent heart attacks, say, and which help bring them on.
